<span style="color: #ffffff;">a. Crowdfunding is aimed at contributing to short term-targets of NGOs</span>

<span style="color: #ffffff;">We are targeting a fundraising of 10 000 euros which would be divided as follow: 50 % for FishReefÂ  Project and 50% for Manengkel Solidaritas.</span>

<span style="color: #ffffff;">b. Corporate donations will contribute to long-term targets of NGOs. Any donation is welcome.</span>

<span style="color: #ffffff;">Scale for Donations: medium â‚¬5000-10000, small &lt; â‚¬5000 , larger &gt; â‚¬10000</span>

<span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #73ffea;">Contact us</span> <span style="color: #ffffff;">for donation proposals and we will assist in the process:</span> <span style="color: #73ffea;"><b>reefitupteam@</b><b>gmail.com</b></span></span>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1557167104370{padding-bottom: 110px !important;background-color: #0a0b4e !important;}"][vc_column enable_content_animation="yes" ca_init_scale_x="1" ca_init_scale_y="1" ca_init_scale_z="1" ca_init_opacity="0" ca_an_scale_x="1" ca_an_scale_y="1" ca_an_scale_z="1" ca_an_opacity="1" offset="vc_col-md-offset-1 vc_col-md-3" ca_init_translate_y="30"][ld_fancy_heading tag="h6" transform="text-uppercase" use_custom_fonts_title="true" color="rgb(115, 255, 234)" fs="14px" lh="1.5em" ls="0.2em" fw="700"]Structure[/ld_fancy_heading][vc_empty_space height="30px"][/vc_column][vc_column offset="vc_col-md-7"][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_column_text]<span style="color: #ffffff;"><strong>Manengkel Solidarita (Indonesia):</strong></span>

<span style="color: #ffffff;">Biological restoration: Following the first stage of the coral transplantation of 240 coral seeds ended in April 2019 and funded by Cargill. the NGO is in need of help for stage 2 of the project: set up monitoring system of the corals and ensure coral traceability for the first year of growth.</span>
<ul>
 	<li><span style="color: #ffffff;">Goal of the funds: make corals that are grown through biological restoration self-sustainable</span></li>
 	<li><span style="color: #ffffff;">Total funds needed: IDR 100 000 000, about â‚¬ 7000</span></li>
 	<li><span style="color: #ffffff;">Time frame for funds: June 2019 - December 2019</span></li>
</ul>
<span style="color: #ffffff;">Fund breakdown: coral monitoring equipment; dive set equipment; local team of divers for monitoring work; 3 dives for coral monitoring in June, September and December 2019.</span>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column][vc_empty_space height="70px"][/vc_column][vc_column enable_content_animation="yes" ca_init_scale_x="1" ca_init_scale_y="1" ca_init_scale_z="1" ca_init_opacity="0" ca_an_scale_x="1" ca_an_scale_y="1" ca_an_scale_z="1" ca_an_opacity="1" offset="vc_col-md-offset-1 vc_col-md-3" ca_init_translate_y="29"][vc_empty_space height="30px"][/vc_column][vc_column enable_content_animation="yes" ca_init_scale_x="1" ca_init_scale_y="1" ca_init_scale_z="1" ca_init_opacity="0" ca_an_scale_x="1" ca_an_scale_y="1" ca_an_scale_z="1" ca_an_opacity="1" offset="vc_col-md-7" ca_init_translate_y="20" ca_duration="1200" ca_delay="150"][vc_column_text]<span style="color: #ffffff;"><strong>FishReef Project (Papua New Guinea):</strong></span>

<span style="color: #ffffff;">Structural restoration: permit for 1500 reef units have been issued by the PNG Government, allowing Fish Reef to create a new coral reef in which each reef unit is proven to carry 400 kgs of marine biomass per year. The NGO is currently deploying 20 reef units pilot project which alone will add 8,000 kgs of marine life.</span>
<ul>
 	<li><span style="color: #ffffff;">Goal of the fund: the NGO needs fund support for the pilot projects of 20 units and initial scale-up stage.</span></li>
 	<li><span style="color: #ffffff;">Total funds needed:Â  â‚¬9000 missing for pilot project up to â‚¬2,6 million for full scale 1500 reef projects.</span></li>
</ul>
<span style="color: #ffffff;">Fund breakdown for pilot project: Cost of marine concrete, Tug boat rental, loca communities monitoring work, community outreach, labour, transport of reef units and reef units permits. total â‚¬27000, â‚¬26000 already raised.</span>

